docblock.long-description:
This class uses Google Maps API to convert addresses (like "1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA") into geographic coordinates (like latitude 37.423021 and longitude -122.083739), which you can use to place markers or position the map.

Usage:

$address = 'Rua Vinte e Quatro de Outubro, 353';
$latLng = \Dz_Geocode::getLatLng($address);

echo 'Latitude: ', $latLng->lat, PHP_EOL;
echo 'Longitude: ', $latLng->lng, PHP_EOL;
